Humans are not alone in this regard, many animals have much wider horizontal field of view compared to vertical. For
example, the Tyrannosaurus rex as with other tyrannosaurids and theropods feature an even greater total field of view:

Fig C: Field of view for Tyrannosaurus and Tarbosaurus

<div>
