    <center><i>Source: [Edaphosaurus](https://twitter.com/Edaphosaurus/status/1582411070517280775)</i></center>
</div>

Sacrificing narrower binocular field of view for more total field of view is a trait attributed to their predatory
nature and evidenced by the eye placement in the skulls of these dinosaurs:

Fig D: A Tyrannosaurus rex pictured making the famous "pogchamp" face
