# Improving WG21 Papers

There's no reason this should be limited to source code, we can apply this same technology to improve papers submitted
to WG21:

<style>
#improve {
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 10px;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    border: 4px solid var(--logo-bg);
    outline: 0 !important;
    font-size: 1.25em;
    cursor: pointer;
}
body.improved {
    writing-mode: vertical-rl;
}
body.improved img,
body.improved svg.math {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
    max-height: 500px;
}
body.improved a.self-link {
    left: 0;
    top: calc(-1 * (3.5rem - 26px));
    transform: rotate(90deg);
}
body.improved .vertical pre {
  writing-mode: horizontal-tb;
}
</style>

<button id="improve">Improve this paper</button>

<script>
document.getElementById("improve").addEventListener("click", () => {
    // toggleSidebar(false);
    if(document.body.classList.contains("toc-sidebar")) {
        document.getElementById("toc-toggle").click();
    }
    document.body.classList.add("improved");
    window.scroll({
        top: 0,
        left: document.body.scrollWidth,
        behavior: "smooth",
    });
}, false);
</script>

